                <dc:creator rdf:resource="https://id.rijksmuseum.nl/2103429" />
                <dc:description xml:lang="en">Already in 1604 the artists’ biographer Karel van Mander advised artists to look in the mirror and practise in the rendering of states of mind. This is what Rembrandt does here. He looks angry, horrified, smiling. Each of these emotions recur in his work. Each of these emotions would recur later in his work.</dc:description>
                <dc:description xml:lang="nl">Al in 1604 raadde schildersbiograaf Karel van Mander kunstenaars aan zichzelf in de spiegel te bekijken en te oefenen in de weergave van gemoedstoestanden. Dat doet Rembrandt hier. Hij kijkt boos, ontzet, of lachend. Stuk voor stuk emoties die later in zijn werk terugkeren.</dc:description>
